        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">HVAC profit margins in 2026 vary dramatically by service type, with emergency repairs hitting 60-70% while new installations struggle to break 20%. Understanding these benchmarks helps you price competitively while maintaining healthy profitability across your service mix.</p>

        <h2 id="overview">HVAC Profit Margin Overview</h2>
        
        <p>The average HVAC company operates on a 12-18% net profit margin, but this number masks significant variations between service types. Companies that track margins by job category consistently outperform those using blanket pricing by 8-12 percentage points.</p>

        <p>Material costs represent 35-45% of total job costs for installations but only 15-25% for service calls. Labor accounts for 25-35% across all service types, while overhead (insurance, vehicles, tools) runs 15-20%. Understanding these cost structures helps optimize pricing for each service category.</p>

