        <h2 id="service-type-margins">Profit Margins by Service Type</h2>

        <p>Service type dramatically impacts profitability. Emergency calls command premium pricing due to urgency, while new construction installations face aggressive bidding pressure. Companies that balance their service mix between high-margin repairs and steady installation work achieve the most consistent profitability.</p>

        <p>The most profitable HVAC companies generate 40-50% of revenue from service and repair calls, 30-40% from replacement installations, and 15-20% from maintenance contracts. This mix provides steady cash flow from contracts while maximizing high-margin emergency work.</p>

        <h2 id="installation-margins">Installation Profit Margins</h2>

        <p>Installation margins have compressed in 2026 due to increased competition and material cost volatility. Residential installations typically run 15-20% margins, while commercial work ranges from 18-25%. Premium installations (high-efficiency systems, smart controls) can achieve 25-35% margins.</p>

        <p>Material costs represent the largest challenge for installation margins. Equipment prices fluctuate 10-15% quarterly based on supply chain conditions. Successful contractors lock in pricing for 30-60 days and adjust quotes weekly to maintain target margins.</p>

        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #1B4F72; margin: 2rem 0;">
          <h3>Installation Margin Breakdown</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Equipment costs:</strong> 40-50% of job total</li>
            <li><strong>Materials (ductwork, electrical):</strong> 15-20% of job total</li>
            <li><strong>Direct labor:</strong> 20-25% of job total</li>
            <li><strong>Overhead allocation:</strong> 8-12% of job total</li>
            <li><strong>Target profit:</strong> 15-25% of job total</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p>Installation efficiency directly impacts margins. Teams that complete jobs in the estimated time achieve target margins, while overruns quickly erode profitability. Top performers use job costing software to track actual vs. estimated hours and identify training needs.</p>

        <h2 id="repair-margins">Repair Service Margins</h2>

        <p>Repair margins consistently outperform installations because material costs are lower and labor rates are higher. Emergency repairs command the highest margins (60-70%) due to urgency pricing, while scheduled repairs run 35-45%.</p>

        <p>Diagnostic fees significantly impact repair margins. Companies charging $89-150 for diagnostics (applied to repairs) achieve 8-12 percentage points higher margins than those offering free diagnostics. The fee covers technician time and filters out price shoppers.</p>

