        <h3>Operational Efficiency</h3>

        <p>Optimize technician routes to reduce drive time and increase billable hours. Companies achieving 6+ billable hours per day maintain target margins more consistently than those averaging 4-5 hours.</p>

        <p>Implement job costing to identify margin leaks. Track actual vs. estimated time and materials for each job category. This data reveals training needs and pricing adjustments worth 3-5% margin improvement.</p>

        <h3>Service Mix Optimization</h3>

        <p>Balance high-margin repairs with steady installation revenue. Target 40-50% repair/service revenue and 35-45% installation revenue for optimal profitability and cash flow.</p>

        <p>Develop maintenance contracts to create predictable revenue streams. Each maintenance customer generates $195-395 annual contract revenue plus 2-3 additional service calls averaging $385 each.</p>

