        <h3>Key Performance Indicators</h3>

        <p>Monitor these metrics monthly to track margin performance:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Gross margin by service type:</strong> Track separately for repairs, installations, and maintenance</li>
          <li><strong>Average ticket size:</strong> Higher tickets typically yield better margins</li>
          <li><strong>Material cost percentage:</strong> Should decrease as margins improve</li>
          <li><strong>Labor efficiency:</strong> Actual vs. estimated hours per job</li>
          <li><strong>Customer acquisition cost:</strong> Lower costs improve overall profitability</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Companies tracking these metrics achieve 8-12% higher margins than those relying on gut instinct for pricing decisions.</p>

        <h3>Competitive Analysis</h3>

        <p>Regular competitive pricing analysis ensures your margins remain competitive while profitable. Call competitors monthly for common repair quotes and adjust pricing to maintain market position within your target margin range.</p>

        <p>Focus on value proposition rather than lowest price. Companies competing on service quality and reliability achieve 15-25% higher margins than price leaders while maintaining strong customer retention.</p>

